hwRsvpTe.contactinfo: Huawei Industrial Base Bantian, Longgang Shenzhen 518129 People's Republic of China Website: http://www.huawei.com Email: support@huawei.com
hwRsvpTe.description: The MIB module to describe the RSVP Protocol
hwRsvpTe.name: hwRsvpTe

revisions.description: V3.00, hwRsvpTeIfStatus from read-only to read-create.
V2.02, add traps: hwRsvpTeIfNbrThresholdExceed, hwRsvpTeIfNbrThresholdExceedClear, hwRsvpTeIfNbrTotalCountExceed, hwRsvpTeIfNbrTotalCountExceedClear.
V2.01, modify the hwRsvpTeTrapObjectGroup of MODULE-COMPLIANCE hwRsvpTeCompliance.

hwRsvpTeAuthFail.description: Indicates neighbour of RSVP hello lost.
hwRsvpTeAuthFail.name: hwRsvpTeAuthFail

hwRsvpTeAuthSuccess.description: Indicates neighbour of RSVP hello lost.
hwRsvpTeAuthSuccess.name: hwRsvpTeAuthSuccess

hwRsvpTeCompliance.description: The compliance statement. Note that the im- plementation of this module requires implemen- tation of the Integrated Services MIB as well.
hwRsvpTeCompliance.name: hwRsvpTeCompliance

hwRsvpTeEroEntry.description: Information describes the ERO sub-objects of an RSVP system.
hwRsvpTeEroEntry.name: hwRsvpTeEroEntry

hwRsvpTeEroIpPrefixLen.description: IP prefix length for this sub-object.
hwRsvpTeEroIpPrefixLen.name: hwRsvpTeEroIpPrefixLen

hwRsvpTeEroNumber.description: The number of this ERO sub-object. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and has no relation to any protocol value.
hwRsvpTeEroNumber.name: hwRsvpTeEroNumber

hwRsvpTeEroTable.description: Information describes the ERO sub-objects of an RSVP system.
hwRsvpTeEroTable.name: hwRsvpTeEroTable

hwRsvpTeEroType.description: An enumerable value that indicates the type of this sub-object. (0x01: IPv4 address; 0x02: IPv6 address.)
hwRsvpTeEroType.name: hwRsvpTeEroType

hwRsvpTeFilterSpecEntry.description: Information describes the FilterSpecs of an RSVP system.
hwRsvpTeFilterSpecEntry.name: hwRsvpTeFilterSpecEntry

hwRsvpTeFilterSpecIngressLsrId.description: IP address for a sender node.
hwRsvpTeFilterSpecIngressLsrId.name: hwRsvpTeFilterSpecIngressLsrId

hwRsvpTeFilterSpecLabel.description: The value of the label arranged by next hop. A return of 4294967295 indicates the absence of the item.
hwRsvpTeFilterSpecLabel.name: hwRsvpTeFilterSpecLabel

hwRsvpTeFilterSpecLspId.description: A 16-bit identifier used in the SENDER_TEMPLATE and the FILTER_SPEC that can be changed to allow a sender to share resources with itself.
hwRsvpTeFilterSpecLspId.name: hwRsvpTeFilterSpecLspId

hwRsvpTeFilterSpecNumber.description: The number of this Filter_Spec. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and has no relation to any protocol value.
hwRsvpTeFilterSpecNumber.name: hwRsvpTeFilterSpecNumber

hwRsvpTeFilterSpecTable.description: Information describes the FilterSpecs of an RSVP system.
hwRsvpTeFilterSpecTable.name: hwRsvpTeFilterSpecTable

hwRsvpTeHelloLost.description: Indicates neighbour of RSVP hello lost.
hwRsvpTeHelloLost.name: hwRsvpTeHelloLost

hwRsvpTeHelloLostRecovery.description: Indicates neighbour of RSVP hello lost.
hwRsvpTeHelloLostRecovery.name: hwRsvpTeHelloLostRecovery

hwRsvpTeIfAuthEnabled.description: If TRUE, authentication is enabled on this interface. If FALSE, authentication is not enabled on this interface.
hwRsvpTeIfAuthEnabled.name: hwRsvpTeIfAuthEnabled

hwRsvpTeIfAuthEncrypted.description: This states that authentication key is encrypted or not.
hwRsvpTeIfAuthEncrypted.name: hwRsvpTeIfAuthEncrypted

hwRsvpTeIfAuthKey.description: Authentication key, used for authentication processing. For security purposes, a get on this returns a zero length string.
hwRsvpTeIfAuthKey.name: hwRsvpTeIfAuthKey

hwRsvpTeIfAuthLifeTime.description: Authentication life time. The default value is 1800000.
hwRsvpTeIfAuthLifeTime.name: hwRsvpTeIfAuthLifeTime

hwRsvpTeIfEnabled.description: Its value is always TRUE, if RSVP is enabled on this Interface.
hwRsvpTeIfEnabled.name: hwRsvpTeIfEnabled

hwRsvpTeIfEntry.description: The RSVP-specific attributes of the a given interface.
hwRsvpTeIfEntry.name: hwRsvpTeIfEntry

hwRsvpTeIfGroup.description: These objects are required for RSVP Systems.
hwRsvpTeIfGroup.name: hwRsvpTeIfGroup

hwRsvpTeIfHelloEnabled.description: If TRUE, RSVPTE hello is enabled on this Interface. If FALSE, RSVPTE hello is not enabled on this interface
hwRsvpTeIfHelloEnabled.name: hwRsvpTeIfHelloEnabled

hwRsvpTeIfIpNbrs.description: The number of neighbors perceived to be using only the RSVP IP Encapsulation.
hwRsvpTeIfIpNbrs.name: hwRsvpTeIfIpNbrs

hwRsvpTeIfName.description: The name of the RSVP interface.
hwRsvpTeIfName.name: hwRsvpTeIfName

hwRsvpTeIfNbrCurrentCount.description: Number of existing neighbors of the RSVP interface.
hwRsvpTeIfNbrCurrentCount.name: hwRsvpTeIfNbrCurrentCount

hwRsvpTeIfNbrThreshold.description: Threshold for the number of neighbors of the RSVP interface.
hwRsvpTeIfNbrThreshold.name: hwRsvpTeIfNbrThreshold

hwRsvpTeIfNbrThresholdExceed.description: Indicates that the number of RSVP interface neighbors has exceeded the upper threshold.
hwRsvpTeIfNbrThresholdExceed.name: hwRsvpTeIfNbrThresholdExceed

hwRsvpTeIfNbrThresholdExceedClear.description: Indicates that the number of RSVP interface neighbors has fallen below the lower threshold.
hwRsvpTeIfNbrThresholdExceedClear.name: hwRsvpTeIfNbrThresholdExceedClear

hwRsvpTeIfNbrTotalCount.description: Maximum number of allowed neighbors of the RSVP interface.
hwRsvpTeIfNbrTotalCount.name: hwRsvpTeIfNbrTotalCount

hwRsvpTeIfNbrTotalCountExceed.description: Indicates that the number of RSVP interface neighbors has reached the maximum number.
hwRsvpTeIfNbrTotalCountExceed.name: hwRsvpTeIfNbrTotalCountExceed

hwRsvpTeIfNbrTotalCountExceedClear.description: Indicates that the number of RSVP interface neighbors has fallen below the recovery number.
hwRsvpTeIfNbrTotalCountExceedClear.name: hwRsvpTeIfNbrTotalCountExceedClear

hwRsvpTeIfNbrs.description: The number of neighbors currently perceived; this will exceed hwRsvpTeIfIpNbrs + hwRsvpTeIfUdpNbrs by the number of neighbors using both encapsu- lations.
hwRsvpTeIfNbrs.name: hwRsvpTeIfNbrs

hwRsvpTeIfRefreshBlockadeMultiple.description: The value of the RSVP value 'Kb', Which is the minimum number of refresh intervals that blockade state will last once entered.
hwRsvpTeIfRefreshBlockadeMultiple.name: hwRsvpTeIfRefreshBlockadeMultiple

hwRsvpTeIfRefreshInterval.description: The value of the RSVP value 'R', which is the minimum period between refresh transmissions of a given PATH or RESV message on an interface. The default value is 30000.
hwRsvpTeIfRefreshInterval.name: hwRsvpTeIfRefreshInterval

hwRsvpTeIfRefreshMultiple.description: The value of the RSVP value 'K', which is the number of refresh intervals which must elapse (minimum) before a PATH or RESV message which is not being refreshed will be aged out.
hwRsvpTeIfRefreshMultiple.name: hwRsvpTeIfRefreshMultiple

hwRsvpTeIfRetranIncDelta.description: Delta governs the speed with which the sender increases the retransmission interval. The ratio of two successive retransmission intervals is (1 + Delta).
hwRsvpTeIfRetranIncDelta.name: hwRsvpTeIfRetranIncDelta

hwRsvpTeIfRetranInterval.description: The retransmission interval. The default value is 5000.
hwRsvpTeIfRetranInterval.name: hwRsvpTeIfRetranInterval

hwRsvpTeIfRouteDelay.description: The approximate period from the time a route is changed to the time a resulting message ap- pears on the interface. The default value is 200.
hwRsvpTeIfRouteDelay.name: hwRsvpTeIfRouteDelay

hwRsvpTeIfSrefreshEnabled.description: If TRUE, srefresh is enabled on this interface. If FALSE, srefresh is not enabled on this interface.
hwRsvpTeIfSrefreshEnabled.name: hwRsvpTeIfSrefreshEnabled

hwRsvpTeIfSrefreshInterval.description: The srefresh interval. I.e. time difference between 2 refreshes. The default value is 30000.
hwRsvpTeIfSrefreshInterval.name: hwRsvpTeIfSrefreshInterval

hwRsvpTeIfStatus.description: 'active' on interfaces that are configured for RSVP.
hwRsvpTeIfStatus.name: hwRsvpTeIfStatus

hwRsvpTeIfTable.description: The RSVP-specific attributes of the system's interfaces.
hwRsvpTeIfTable.name: hwRsvpTeIfTable

hwRsvpTeIfTtl.description: The value of SEND_TTL used on this interface for messages this node originates. If set to zero, the node determines the TTL via other means.
hwRsvpTeIfTtl.name: hwRsvpTeIfTtl

hwRsvpTeIfUdpNbrs.description: The number of neighbors perceived to be using only the RSVP UDP Encapsulation.
hwRsvpTeIfUdpNbrs.name: hwRsvpTeIfUdpNbrs

hwRsvpTeIfUdpRequired.description: If TRUE, manual configuration forces the use of UDP encapsulation on the interface. If FALSE, UDP encapsulation is only used if hwRsvpTeI- fUdpNbrs is not zero.
hwRsvpTeIfUdpRequired.name: hwRsvpTeIfUdpRequired

hwRsvpTeIfWindowSize.description: Administrators can specify a message window corresponding to the worst case reordering behavior. For example, one might specify that packets reordered within a 32 message window would be accepted. If no reordering can occur, the window is set to one. The maximum value is 64. The default value is 1.
hwRsvpTeIfWindowSize.name: hwRsvpTeIfWindowSize

hwRsvpTeLspId.description: A 16-bit identifier used in the SENDER_TEMPLATE and the FILTER_SPEC that can be changed to allow a sender to share resources with itself.
hwRsvpTeLspId.name: hwRsvpTeLspId

hwRsvpTeMessageIdEntry.description: Information describes the MessageIds of an RSVP system.
hwRsvpTeMessageIdEntry.name: hwRsvpTeMessageIdEntry

hwRsvpTeMessageIdEpoch.description: A value that indicates when the Message_Identi- fier sequence has been reset.
hwRsvpTeMessageIdEpoch.name: hwRsvpTeMessageIdEpoch

hwRsvpTeMessageIdFlag.description: A enumerable value to indicate the type of this Message_Identifier. (1: SenderIncoming; 2: SenderOutgoing; 3: Resv; 4: ResvFwd; 5: RtBuff)
hwRsvpTeMessageIdFlag.name: hwRsvpTeMessageIdFlag

hwRsvpTeMessageIdNumber.description: When combined with the message generator's IP address, the Message_Identifier field uniquely identifies a message. The values placed in this field change incrementally and only decrease when the epoch changes or when the value wraps.
hwRsvpTeMessageIdNumber.name: hwRsvpTeMessageIdNumber

hwRsvpTeMessageIdTable.description: Information describes the MessageIds of an RSVP system.
hwRsvpTeMessageIdTable.name: hwRsvpTeMessageIdTable

hwRsvpTeNbrAddress.description: The IP4 or IP6 Address used by this neighbor. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'active'.
hwRsvpTeNbrAddress.name: hwRsvpTeNbrAddress

hwRsvpTeNbrAuthKeyId.description: Neighbor's authentication key, used for authentication processing. A return of null string indicates the absence of the item. For security purposes, a get on this returns a zero length string.
hwRsvpTeNbrAuthKeyId.name: hwRsvpTeNbrAuthKeyId

hwRsvpTeNbrEntry.description: Information describing a single RSVP Neigh- bor.
hwRsvpTeNbrEntry.name: hwRsvpTeNbrEntry

hwRsvpTeNbrGrCapability.description: Gives neighbor capability to support GR or undergo GR, in case of control plane restart. A mixed value. (0x01: Self GR capability of neighbor; 0x02: GR support capability of neighbor; 0x04: Neighbor capable of receiving RecoveryPath message; 0x08: Neighbor capable of sending RecoveryPath message)
hwRsvpTeNbrGrCapability.name: hwRsvpTeNbrGrCapability

hwRsvpTeNbrGrRecoveryTime.description: Neighbor nodes GR recovery time value.
hwRsvpTeNbrGrRecoveryTime.name: hwRsvpTeNbrGrRecoveryTime

hwRsvpTeNbrGrRestartTime.description: Neighbor nodes GR restart time value.
hwRsvpTeNbrGrRestartTime.name: hwRsvpTeNbrGrRestartTime

hwRsvpTeNbrGrStatus.description: Neighbor nodes GR status. (0x01, No GR activity; 0x02, Neighbor router is supporting GR; 0x03, Neighbor router is restarting; 0x04, Restart timer is running; 0x05, Recovery timer is running; 0x06, Neighbor GR end.)
hwRsvpTeNbrGrStatus.name: hwRsvpTeNbrGrStatus

hwRsvpTeNbrGroup.description: These objects are required for RSVP Systems.
hwRsvpTeNbrGroup.name: hwRsvpTeNbrGroup

hwRsvpTeNbrHelloEnabled.description: If TRUE, hello is enabled on the neighbor.
hwRsvpTeNbrHelloEnabled.name: hwRsvpTeNbrHelloEnabled

hwRsvpTeNbrHelloLostCounter.description: The number of times the hello messages have been sent to the neighbor for which hello ACK has not received yet.
hwRsvpTeNbrHelloLostCounter.name: hwRsvpTeNbrHelloLostCounter

hwRsvpTeNbrHelloType.description: Hello type that is being sent to the neighbor. A return of 3[none] indicates that hello is disabled on the nbr.
hwRsvpTeNbrHelloType.name: hwRsvpTeNbrHelloType

hwRsvpTeNbrProtocol.description: The encapsulation being used by this neigh- bor.
hwRsvpTeNbrProtocol.name: hwRsvpTeNbrProtocol

hwRsvpTeNbrReceiversNumber.description: The number of receivers on the neighbor.
hwRsvpTeNbrReceiversNumber.name: hwRsvpTeNbrReceiversNumber

hwRsvpTeNbrReductionEnabled.description: If TRUE srefresh is enabled on the neighbor, else srefresh is not enabled on the neighbor.
hwRsvpTeNbrReductionEnabled.name: hwRsvpTeNbrReductionEnabled

hwRsvpTeNbrReliabilityEnabled.description: If TRUE reliability is enabled on the neighbor, else reliability is not enabled on the neighbor.
hwRsvpTeNbrReliabilityEnabled.name: hwRsvpTeNbrReliabilityEnabled

hwRsvpTeNbrSendersNumber.description: The number of senders on the neighbor.
hwRsvpTeNbrSendersNumber.name: hwRsvpTeNbrSendersNumber

hwRsvpTeNbrStatus.description: 'active' for all neighbors. This object may be used to configure neighbors. In the pres- ence of configured neighbors, the implementa- tion may (but is not required to) limit the set of valid neighbors to those configured.
hwRsvpTeNbrStatus.name: hwRsvpTeNbrStatus

hwRsvpTeNbrTable.description: Information describing the Neighbors of an RSVP system.
hwRsvpTeNbrTable.name: hwRsvpTeNbrTable

hwRsvpTeResvDestAddr.description: The destination address used by all senders in this session.
hwRsvpTeResvDestAddr.name: hwRsvpTeResvDestAddr

hwRsvpTeResvDestAddrLength.description: The length of the destination address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits.
hwRsvpTeResvDestAddrLength.name: hwRsvpTeResvDestAddrLength

hwRsvpTeResvEntry.description: Information describing the state information displayed by a single receiver's RESV message concerning a single sender.
hwRsvpTeResvEntry.name: hwRsvpTeResvEntry

hwRsvpTeResvExplicit.description: If TRUE, individual senders are listed using Filter Specifications. If FALSE, all senders are implicitly selected. The Scope Object will contain a list of senders that need to receive this reservation request for the purpose of routing the RESV message.
hwRsvpTeResvExplicit.name: hwRsvpTeResvExplicit

hwRsvpTeResvFwdDestAddr.description: The destination address used by all senders in this session.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdDestAddr.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdDestAddr

hwRsvpTeResvFwdDestAddrLength.description: The length of the destination address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdDestAddrLength.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdDestAddrLength

hwRsvpTeResvFwdEntry.description: Information describing the state information displayed upstream in an RESV message concern- ing a single sender.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdEntry.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdEntry

hwRsvpTeResvFwdExplicit.description: If TRUE, individual senders are listed using Filter Specifications. If FALSE, all senders are implicitly selected. The Scope Object will contain a list of senders that need to receive this reservation request for the purpose of routing the RESV message.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdExplicit.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdExplicit

hwRsvpTeResvFwdGroup.description: These objects are optional, used for some RSVP Systems.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdGroup.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdGroup

hwRsvpTeResvFwdHopAddr.description: The address of the (previous) RSVP that will receive this message.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdHopAddr.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdHopAddr

hwRsvpTeResvFwdHopLih.description: The Logical Interface Handle sent to the (pre- vious) RSVP that will receive this message.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdHopLih.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdHopLih

hwRsvpTeResvFwdInterface.description: The ifIndex value of the interface on which this RESV message was most recently sent.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdInterface.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdInterface

hwRsvpTeResvFwdInterval.description: The interval between refresh messages adver- tised to the Previous Hop.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdInterval.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdInterval

hwRsvpTeResvFwdMsgIdEpoch.description: A value that indicates when the Message_Identi- fier sequence has been reset.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdMsgIdEpoch.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdMsgIdEpoch

hwRsvpTeResvFwdMsgIdFlag.description: Indicates that the message sender requests the peer to send an acknowledgment for the message. (0x01: ACK desired.)
hwRsvpTeResvFwdMsgIdFlag.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdMsgIdFlag

hwRsvpTeResvFwdMsgIdNumber.description: When combined with the message generator's IP address, the Message_Identifier field uniquely identifies a message. The values placed in this field change incrementally and only decrease when the epoch changes or when the value wraps. A return of 0 indicates the absence of the MESSAGE_ID object.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdMsgIdNumber.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdMsgIdNumber

hwRsvpTeResvFwdNumber.description: The number of this reservation request. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and has no relation to any protocol value.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdNumber.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdNumber

hwRsvpTeResvFwdPolicy.description: The contents of the policy object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdPolicy.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdPolicy

hwRsvpTeResvFwdRSpecRate.description: If the requested service is Guaranteed, as specified by hwRsvpTeResvService, this is the clearing rate that is being requested. Other- wise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdRSpecRate.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdRSpecRate

hwRsvpTeResvFwdRSpecSlack.description: If the requested service is Guaranteed, as specified by hwRsvpTeResvService, this is the delay slack. Otherwise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdRSpecSlack.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdRSpecSlack

hwRsvpTeResvFwdRsvpHop.description: If TRUE, the node believes that the next IP hop is an RSVP hop. If FALSE, the node be- lieves that the next IP hop may not be an RSVP hop.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdRsvpHop.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdRsvpHop

hwRsvpTeResvFwdScope.description: The contents of the scope object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdScope.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdScope

hwRsvpTeResvFwdSenderAddr.description: The source address of the sender selected by this reservation. The value of all zeroes in- dicates 'all senders'.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdSenderAddr.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdSenderAddr

hwRsvpTeResvFwdSenderAddrLength.description: The length of the sender's address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdSenderAddrLength.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdSenderAddrLength

hwRsvpTeResvFwdShared.description: If TRUE, a reservation shared among senders is requested. If FALSE, a reservation specific to this sender is requested.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdShared.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdShared

hwRsvpTeResvFwdTSpecBurst.description: The size of the largest burst expected from the sender at a time. If this is less than the sender's advertised burst size, the receiver is asking the network to provide flow pacing beyond what would be provided under normal circumstances. Such pac- ing is at the network's option.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdTSpecBurst.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdTSpecBurst

hwRsvpTeResvFwdTSpecMaxTu.description: The maximum message size for this flow. The admission algorithm will reject TSpecs whose Maximum Transmission Unit, plus the interface headers, exceed the interface MTU.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdTSpecMaxTu.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdTSpecMaxTu

hwRsvpTeResvFwdTSpecMinTu.description: The minimum message size for this flow. The policing algorithm will treat smaller messages as though they are this size.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdTSpecMinTu.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdTSpecMinTu

hwRsvpTeResvFwdTSpecPeakRate.description: The Peak Bit Rate of the sender's data stream Traffic arrival is not expected to exceed this rate at any time, apart from the effects of jitter in the network. If not specified in the TSpec, this returns zero or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdTSpecPeakRate.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdTSpecPeakRate

hwRsvpTeResvFwdTSpecRate.description: The Average Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Within a transmission burst, the ar- rival rate may be as fast as hwRsvpTeResvFwdT- SpecPeakRate (if supported by the service model);however, averaged across two or more burst intervals, the rate should not exceed hwRsvpTeResvFwdTSpecRate. Note that this is a prediction, often based on the general capability of a type of codec or particular encoding; the measured average rate may be significantly lower.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdTSpecRate.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdTSpecRate

hwRsvpTeResvFwdTable.description: Information describing the state information displayed upstream in RESV messages.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdTable.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdTable

hwRsvpTeResvFwdTtl.description: The TTL value in the RSVP header that was last received.
hwRsvpTeResvFwdTtl.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdTtl

hwRsvpTeResvFwdType.description: The type of session (IP4, IP6, IP6 with flow information, etc).
hwRsvpTeResvFwdType.name: hwRsvpTeResvFwdType

hwRsvpTeResvGroup.description: These objects are required for RSVP Systems.
hwRsvpTeResvGroup.name: hwRsvpTeResvGroup

hwRsvpTeResvHopAddr.description: The address used by the next RSVP hop (which may be the ultimate receiver).
hwRsvpTeResvHopAddr.name: hwRsvpTeResvHopAddr

hwRsvpTeResvHopLih.description: The Logical Interface Handle received from the previous RSVP hop (which may be the ultimate receiver).
hwRsvpTeResvHopLih.name: hwRsvpTeResvHopLih

hwRsvpTeResvInterface.description: The ifIndex value of the interface on which this RESV message was most recently received.
hwRsvpTeResvInterface.name: hwRsvpTeResvInterface

hwRsvpTeResvInterval.description: The interval between refresh messages as ad- vertised by the Next Hop.
hwRsvpTeResvInterval.name: hwRsvpTeResvInterval

hwRsvpTeResvNumber.description: The number of this reservation request. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and has no relation to any protocol value.
hwRsvpTeResvNumber.name: hwRsvpTeResvNumber

hwRsvpTeResvPolicy.description: The contents of the policy object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length.
hwRsvpTeResvPolicy.name: hwRsvpTeResvPolicy

hwRsvpTeResvRSpecRate.description: If the requested service is guaranteed, as specified by hwRsvpTeResvService, this is the clearing rate that is being requested. Other- wise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeResvRSpecRate.name: hwRsvpTeResvRSpecRate

hwRsvpTeResvRSpecSlack.description: If the requested service is guaranteed, as specified by hwRsvpTeResvService, this is the delay slack. Otherwise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeResvRSpecSlack.name: hwRsvpTeResvRSpecSlack

hwRsvpTeResvRsvpHop.description: If TRUE, the node believes that the previous IP hop is an RSVP hop. If FALSE, the node be- lieves that the previous IP hop may not be an RSVP hop.
hwRsvpTeResvRsvpHop.name: hwRsvpTeResvRsvpHop

hwRsvpTeResvScope.description: The contents of the scope object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length. If the length is non-zero, this contains a series of IP4 or IP6 addresses.
hwRsvpTeResvScope.name: hwRsvpTeResvScope

hwRsvpTeResvSenderAddr.description: The source address of the sender selected by this reservation. The value of all zeroes in- dicates 'all senders'.
hwRsvpTeResvSenderAddr.name: hwRsvpTeResvSenderAddr

hwRsvpTeResvSenderAddrLength.description: The length of the sender's address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits.
hwRsvpTeResvSenderAddrLength.name: hwRsvpTeResvSenderAddrLength

hwRsvpTeResvService.description: The QoS Service classification requested by the receiver.
hwRsvpTeResvService.name: hwRsvpTeResvService

hwRsvpTeResvShared.description: If TRUE, a reservation shared among senders is requested. If FALSE, a reservation specific to this sender is requested.
hwRsvpTeResvShared.name: hwRsvpTeResvShared

hwRsvpTeResvTSpecBurst.description: The size of the largest burst expected from the sender at a time. If this is less than the sender's advertised burst size, the receiver is asking the network to provide flow pacing beyond what would be provided under normal circumstances. Such pac- ing is at the network's option.
hwRsvpTeResvTSpecBurst.name: hwRsvpTeResvTSpecBurst

hwRsvpTeResvTSpecMaxTu.description: The maximum message size for this flow. The admission algorithm will reject TSpecs whose Maximum Transmission Unit, plus the interface headers, exceed the interface MTU.
hwRsvpTeResvTSpecMaxTu.name: hwRsvpTeResvTSpecMaxTu

hwRsvpTeResvTSpecMinTu.description: The minimum message size for this flow. The policing algorithm will treat smaller messages as though they are this size.
hwRsvpTeResvTSpecMinTu.name: hwRsvpTeResvTSpecMinTu

hwRsvpTeResvTSpecPeakRate.description: The Peak Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Traffic arrival is not expected to exceed this rate at any time, apart from the effects of jitter in the network. If not specified in the TSpec, this returns zero or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeResvTSpecPeakRate.name: hwRsvpTeResvTSpecPeakRate

hwRsvpTeResvTSpecRate.description: The Average Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Within a transmission burst, the ar- rival rate may be as fast as hwRsvpTeResvTSpec- PeakRate (if supported by the service model); however, averaged across two or more burst in- tervals, the rate should not exceed hwRsvpTeResvTSpecRate. Note that this is a prediction, often based on the general capability of a type of codec or particular encoding; the measured average rate may be significantly lower.
hwRsvpTeResvTSpecRate.name: hwRsvpTeResvTSpecRate

hwRsvpTeResvTable.description: Information describing the state information displayed by receivers in RESV messages.
hwRsvpTeResvTable.name: hwRsvpTeResvTable

hwRsvpTeResvTtl.description: The TTL value in the RSVP header that was last received.
hwRsvpTeResvTtl.name: hwRsvpTeResvTtl

hwRsvpTeResvType.description: The type of session (IP4, IP6, IP6 with flow information, etc).
hwRsvpTeResvType.name: hwRsvpTeResvType

hwRsvpTeRroEntry.description: Information describes the RRO sub-objects of an RSVP system.
hwRsvpTeRroEntry.name: hwRsvpTeRroEntry

hwRsvpTeRroFlag.description: If hwRsvpTeRroType is IPv4 or IPv6, it is a mixed value. (0x01: Local protection available; 0x02: Local protection in use; 0x04: bandwidth protection; 0x08: node protection; 0x10: preemption pending; 0x20: node ID.) If hwRsvpTeRroType is Label, 0x01 means global label. A return of zero indicates no bit was set.
hwRsvpTeRroFlag.name: hwRsvpTeRroFlag

hwRsvpTeRroIpAddr.description: IP address for this sub-object if the type is 'IPv4 address' of 'IPv6 address'. A return of null string indicates the absence of the item.
hwRsvpTeRroIpAddr.name: hwRsvpTeRroIpAddr

hwRsvpTeRroIpPrefixLen.description: IP prefix length for this sub-object if the type is 'IPv4 address' of 'IPv6 address'. A return of 0 indicates the absence of the item.
hwRsvpTeRroIpPrefixLen.name: hwRsvpTeRroIpPrefixLen

hwRsvpTeRroLabel.description: The value of the label if the type is 'Label'. A return of 4294967295 indicates the absence of the item.
hwRsvpTeRroLabel.name: hwRsvpTeRroLabel

hwRsvpTeRroNumber.description: The number of this RRO sub-object. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and has no relation to any protocol value.
hwRsvpTeRroNumber.name: hwRsvpTeRroNumber

hwRsvpTeRroTable.description: Information describes the RRO sub-objects of an RSVP system.
hwRsvpTeRroTable.name: hwRsvpTeRroTable

hwRsvpTeRroType.description: An enumerable value that indicates the type of this sub-object. (0x01: IPv4 address; 0x02: IPv6 address; 0x03: Label.)
hwRsvpTeRroType.name: hwRsvpTeRroType

hwRsvpTeSenderAddr.description: The source address used by this sender in this session.
hwRsvpTeSenderAddr.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAddr

hwRsvpTeSenderAddrLength.description: The length of the sender's address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits.
hwRsvpTeSenderAddrLength.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAddrLength

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecBreak.description: The global break bit general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. If TRUE, at least one non-IS hop was detected in the path. If FALSE, no non-IS hops were detected.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecBreak.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecBreak

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadBreak.description: If TRUE, the Controlled Load Service fragment has its 'break' bit set, indicating that one or more nodes along the path do not support the controlled load service. If FALSE, and hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is TRUE, the 'break' bit is not set. If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is FALSE, this returns FALSE or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadBreak.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadBreak

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadHopCount.description: If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the hop count general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadHopCount.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadHopCount

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadMinLatency.description: If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the minimum path latency general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuch- Value indicates one of the following condi- tions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadMinLatency.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadMinLatency

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadMtu.description: If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the com- posed Maximum Transmission Unit general charac- terization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadMtu.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadMtu

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadPathBw.description: If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the path bandwidth estimate general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following con- ditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadPathBw.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadPathBw

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc.description: If TRUE, the ADSPEC contains a Controlled Load Service fragment. If FALSE, the ADSPEC does not contain a Controlled Load Service frag- ment.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecCtrlLoadSvc

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedBreak.description: If TRUE, the Guaranteed Service fragment has its 'break' bit set, indicating that one or more nodes along the path do not support the guaranteed service. If FALSE, and hwRsvpTe- SenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, the 'break' bit is not set. If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns FALSE or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedBreak.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedBreak

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedCsum.description: If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, this is the composed value for the guaranteed ser- vice 'C' parameter since the last reshaping point. A return of zero or noSuchValue indi- cates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedCsum.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedCsum

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedCtot.description: If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, this is the end-to-end composed value for the guaranteed service 'C' parameter. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the fol- lowing conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedCtot.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedCtot

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedDsum.description: If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, this is the composed value for the guaranteed ser- vice 'D' parameter since the last reshaping point. A return of zero or noSuchValue indi- cates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedDsum.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedDsum

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedDtot.description: If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, this is the end-to-end composed value for the guaranteed service 'D' parameter. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the fol- lowing conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedDtot.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedDtot

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedHopCount.description: If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the hop count general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedHopCount.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedHopCount

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedMinLatency.description: If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the minimum path latency general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuch- Value indicates one of the following condi- tions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedMinLatency.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedMinLatency

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedMtu.description: If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the com- posed Maximum Transmission Unit general charac- terization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedMtu.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedMtu

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedPathBw.description: If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the path bandwidth estimate general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following con- ditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedPathBw.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedPathBw

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc.description: If TRUE, the ADSPEC contains a Guaranteed Ser- vice fragment. If FALSE, the ADSPEC does not contain a Guaranteed Service fragment.
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecHopCount.description: The hop count general characterization parame- ter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following con- ditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecHopCount.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecHopCount

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecMinLatency.description: The minimum path latency general characteriza- tion parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the fol- lowing conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecMinLatency.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecMinLatency

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecMtu.description: The composed Maximum Transmission Unit general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecMtu.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecMtu

hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecPathBw.description: The path bandwidth estimate general character- ization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the fol- lowing conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present
hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecPathBw.name: hwRsvpTeSenderAdspecPathBw

hwRsvpTeSenderClassType.description: Indicates the class-type. A return of zero indicates the absence of the object.
hwRsvpTeSenderClassType.name: hwRsvpTeSenderClassType

hwRsvpTeSenderDestAddr.description: The destination address used by all senders in this session.
hwRsvpTeSenderDestAddr.name: hwRsvpTeSenderDestAddr

hwRsvpTeSenderDestAddrLength.description: The length of the destination address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits.
hwRsvpTeSenderDestAddrLength.name: hwRsvpTeSenderDestAddrLength

hwRsvpTeSenderDiffServPsc.description: This 16 bits field indicates a PHB Scheduling Class to be supported by the LSP.
hwRsvpTeSenderDiffServPsc.name: hwRsvpTeSenderDiffServPsc

hwRsvpTeSenderEntry.description: Information describing the state information displayed by a single sender's PATH message.
hwRsvpTeSenderEntry.name: hwRsvpTeSenderEntry

hwRsvpTeSenderFrrBandwidth.description: Bandwidth estimate; 32-bit IEEE floating point integer, in bits per second.
hwRsvpTeSenderFrrBandwidth.name: hwRsvpTeSenderFrrBandwidth

hwRsvpTeSenderFrrExcludeAny.description: A 32-bit vector representing a set of attribute filters associated with a backup path, any of which renders a link unacceptable.
hwRsvpTeSenderFrrExcludeAny.name: hwRsvpTeSenderFrrExcludeAny

hwRsvpTeSenderFrrFlag.description: An enumerable value to indicate the protection schema desired (0x01, One-to-One Backup Desired; 0x02, Facility Backup Desired; 0x03, No Backup Desired).
hwRsvpTeSenderFrrFlag.name: hwRsvpTeSenderFrrFlag

hwRsvpTeSenderFrrHoldPrio.description: The priority of the backup path with respect to holding resources, in the range 0 to 7. The value 0 is the highest priority. Holding Priority is used in deciding whether this session can be preempted by another session. The default value is 7.
hwRsvpTeSenderFrrHoldPrio.name: hwRsvpTeSenderFrrHoldPrio

hwRsvpTeSenderFrrHopLimit.description: The maximum number of extra hops the backup path is allowed to take, from current node (a PLR) to an MP, with PLR and MP excluded from the count. For example, hop-limit of 0 means that only direct links between PLR and MP can be considered. The default value is 16.
hwRsvpTeSenderFrrHopLimit.name: hwRsvpTeSenderFrrHopLimit

hwRsvpTeSenderFrrIncludeAll.description: A 32-bit vector representing a set of attribute filters associated with a backup path, all of which must be present for a link to be acceptable (with respect to this test). A null set (all bits set to zero) automatically passes.
hwRsvpTeSenderFrrIncludeAll.name: hwRsvpTeSenderFrrIncludeAll

hwRsvpTeSenderFrrIncludeAny.description: A 32-bit vector representing a set of attribute filters associated with a backup path, any of which renders a link acceptable (with respect to this test). A null set (all bits set to zero) automatically passes.
hwRsvpTeSenderFrrIncludeAny.name: hwRsvpTeSenderFrrIncludeAny

hwRsvpTeSenderFrrInuseFlag.description: An enumerable value to indicate the fast-reroute state of this sender (normal, PLR in use, MP in use, PLR in use and MP in use, under protection).
hwRsvpTeSenderFrrInuseFlag.name: hwRsvpTeSenderFrrInuseFlag

hwRsvpTeSenderFrrSetupPrio.description: The priority of the backup path with respect to taking resources, in the range 0 to 7. The value 0 is the highest priority. Setup Priority is used in deciding whether this session can preempt another session. See [RSVP-TE] for the usage on priority. The default value is 7.
hwRsvpTeSenderFrrSetupPrio.name: hwRsvpTeSenderFrrSetupPrio

hwRsvpTeSenderGroup.description: These objects are required for RSVP Systems.
hwRsvpTeSenderGroup.name: hwRsvpTeSenderGroup

hwRsvpTeSenderHopAddr.description: The address used by the previous RSVP hop (which may be the original sender).
hwRsvpTeSenderHopAddr.name: hwRsvpTeSenderHopAddr

hwRsvpTeSenderHopLih.description: The Logical Interface Handle used by the pre- vious RSVP hop (which may be the original sender).
hwRsvpTeSenderHopLih.name: hwRsvpTeSenderHopLih

hwRsvpTeSenderInterface.description: The ifIndex value of the interface on which this PATH message was most recently received.
hwRsvpTeSenderInterface.name: hwRsvpTeSenderInterface

hwRsvpTeSenderInterval.description: The interval between refresh messages as ad- vertised by the previous hop.
hwRsvpTeSenderInterval.name: hwRsvpTeSenderInterval

hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestAtmMaxVci.description: This 16 bit field specifies the upper bound of a block of Virtual Connection Identifiers that is supported on the originating switch. If the VCI is less than 16-bits it must be right justified in this field and preceding bits must be set to zero.
hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestAtmMaxVci.name: hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestAtmMaxVci

hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestAtmMaxVpi.description: This 12 bit field specifies the upper bound of a block of Virtual Path Identifiers that is supported on the originating switch. If the VPI is less than 12-bits it must be right justified in this field and preceding bits must be set to zero.
hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestAtmMaxVpi.name: hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestAtmMaxVpi

hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestAtmMinVci.description: This 16 bit field specifies the lower bound of a block of Virtual Connection Identifiers that is supported on the originating switch. If the VCI is less than 16-bits it must be right justified in this field and preceding bits must be set to zero.
hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestAtmMinVci.name: hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestAtmMinVci

hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestAtmMinVpi.description: This 12 bit field specifies the lower bound of a block of Virtual Path Identifiers that is supported on the originating switch. If the VPI is less than 12-bits it must be right justified in this field and preceding bits must be set to zero.
hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestAtmMinVpi.name: hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestAtmMinVpi

hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestCtype.description: The type of label request (without label range, with ATM label range, with frame relay label range, etc).
hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestCtype.name: hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestCtype

hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestFrMaxDlci.description: This 23-bit field specifies the upper bound of a block of Data Link Connection Identifiers (DLCIs) that is supported on the originating switch. The DLCI must be right justified in this field and unused bits must be set to 0.
hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestFrMaxDlci.name: hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestFrMaxDlci

hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestFrMinDlci.description: This 23-bit field specifies the lower bound of a block of Data Link Connection Identifiers (DLCIs) that is supported on the originating switch. The DLCI must be right justified in this field and unused bits must be set to 0.
hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestFrMinDlci.name: hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestFrMinDlci

hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestL3pid.description: An identifier of the layer 3 protocol using this path. Standard Ethertype values are used.
hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestL3pid.name: hwRsvpTeSenderLabelRequestL3pid

hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdRcvEpoch.description: The message ID epoch of the message latest received form the interface.
hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdRcvEpoch.name: hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdRcvEpoch

hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdRcvFlag.description: The message ID flag of the message latest received. It is used to identify whether ACK is desired or not. And it can be extended. (0x01: ACK desired.)
hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdRcvFlag.name: hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdRcvFlag

hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdRcvNumber.description: The message ID number of the message latest received form the interface. A return of 0 indicates the absence of the MESSAGE_ID object received.
hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdRcvNumber.name: hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdRcvNumber

hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdSndEpoch.description: A value that indicates when the Message_Identi- fier sequence has been reset.
hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdSndEpoch.name: hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdSndEpoch

hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdSndFlag.description: Indicates that the message sender requests the peer to send an acknowledgment for the message. (0x01: ACK desired.)
hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdSndFlag.name: hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdSndFlag

hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdSndNumber.description: When combined with the message generator's IP address, the Message_Identifier field uniquely identifies a message. The values placed in this field change incrementally and only decrease when the Epoch changes or when the value wraps. A return of 0 indicates the absence of the MESSAGE_ID object to be sent.
hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdSndNumber.name: hwRsvpTeSenderMsgIdSndNumber

hwRsvpTeSenderNumber.description: The number of this sender. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and has no relation to any protocol value.
hwRsvpTeSenderNumber.name: hwRsvpTeSenderNumber

hwRsvpTeSenderPolicy.description: The contents of the policy object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length.
hwRsvpTeSenderPolicy.name: hwRsvpTeSenderPolicy

hwRsvpTeSenderRsvpHop.description: If TRUE, the node believes that the previous IP hop is an RSVP hop. If FALSE, the node be- lieves that the previous IP hop may not be an RSVP hop.
hwRsvpTeSenderRsvpHop.name: hwRsvpTeSenderRsvpHop

hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrExcludeAny.description: A 32-bit vector representing a set of attribute filters associated with a tunnel any of which renders a link unacceptable.
hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrExcludeAny.name: hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrExcludeAny

hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrFlag.description: A mixed value. (0x01: Local protection desired; 0x02: Label recording desired; 0x04: SE Style desired; 0x08: bandwidth protection desired; 0x10: node protection desired; 0x20: Path re-evaluation request; 0x40: Soft preemption desired)
hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrFlag.name: hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrFlag

hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrHoldPrio.description: The priority of the session with respect to holding resources, in the range of 0 to 7. The value 0 is the highest priority. Holding Priority is used in deciding whether this session can be preempted by another session. The default value is 7.
hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrHoldPrio.name: hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrHoldPrio

hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrIncludeAll.description: A 32-bit vector representing a set of attribute filters associated with a tunnel all of which must be present for a link to be acceptable (with respect to this test). A null set (all bits set to zero) automatically passes.
hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrIncludeAll.name: hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrIncludeAll

hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrIncludeAny.description: A 32-bit vector representing a set of attribute filters associated with a tunnel any of which renders a link acceptable (with respect to this test). A null set (all bits set to zero) automatically passes.
hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrIncludeAny.name: hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrIncludeAny

hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrName.description: Session name, a null padded string of characters.
hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrName.name: hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrName

hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrSetupPrio.description: The priority of the session with respect to taking resources, in the range of 0 to 7. The value 0 is the highest priority. The Setup Priority is used in deciding whether this session can preempt another session. The default value is 7.
hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrSetupPrio.name: hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrSetupPrio

hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrType.description: The type of the session_attribute (without resource affinities or with resource affinities).
hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrType.name: hwRsvpTeSenderSessionAttrType

hwRsvpTeSenderTSpecBurst.description: The size of the largest burst expected from the sender at a time.
hwRsvpTeSenderTSpecBurst.name: hwRsvpTeSenderTSpecBurst

hwRsvpTeSenderTSpecMaxTu.description: The maximum message size for this flow. The admission algorithm will reject TSpecs whose Maximum Transmission Unit, plus the interface headers, exceed the interface MTU.
hwRsvpTeSenderTSpecMaxTu.name: hwRsvpTeSenderTSpecMaxTu

hwRsvpTeSenderTSpecMinTu.description: The minimum message size for this flow. The policing algorithm will treat smaller messages as though they are this size.
hwRsvpTeSenderTSpecMinTu.name: hwRsvpTeSenderTSpecMinTu

hwRsvpTeSenderTSpecPeakRate.description: The Peak Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Traffic arrival is not expected to exceed this rate at any time, apart from the effects of jitter in the network. If not specified in the TSpec, this returns zero or noSuchValue.
hwRsvpTeSenderTSpecPeakRate.name: hwRsvpTeSenderTSpecPeakRate

hwRsvpTeSenderTSpecRate.description: The Average Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Within a transmission burst, the ar- rival rate may be as fast as hwRsvpTeSenderTSpec- PeakRate (if supported by the service model); however, averaged across two or more burst in- tervals, the rate should not exceed hwRsvpTeSen- derTSpecRate. Note that this is a prediction, often based on the general capability of a type of codec or particular encoding; the measured average rate may be significantly lower.
hwRsvpTeSenderTSpecRate.name: hwRsvpTeSenderTSpecRate

hwRsvpTeSenderTable.description: Information describing the state information displayed by senders in PATH messages.
hwRsvpTeSenderTable.name: hwRsvpTeSenderTable

hwRsvpTeSenderTtl.description: The TTL value in the RSVP header that was last received.
hwRsvpTeSenderTtl.name: hwRsvpTeSenderTtl

hwRsvpTeSenderType.description: The type of session (IP4, IP6, IP6 with flow information, etc).
hwRsvpTeSenderType.name: hwRsvpTeSenderType

hwRsvpTeSessionDestAddr.description: The destination address used by all senders in this session.
hwRsvpTeSessionDestAddr.name: hwRsvpTeSessionDestAddr

hwRsvpTeSessionDestAddrLength.description: The CIDR prefix length of the session address, which is 32 for IP4 host and multicast ad- dresses, and 128 for IP6 addresses.
hwRsvpTeSessionDestAddrLength.name: hwRsvpTeSessionDestAddrLength

hwRsvpTeSessionEntry.description: A single session seen by a given system.
hwRsvpTeSessionEntry.name: hwRsvpTeSessionEntry

hwRsvpTeSessionGroup.description: These objects are required for RSVP Systems.
hwRsvpTeSessionGroup.name: hwRsvpTeSessionGroup

hwRsvpTeSessionLspsNumber.description: The number of LSPs that belong to this session.
hwRsvpTeSessionLspsNumber.name: hwRsvpTeSessionLspsNumber

hwRsvpTeSessionNumber.description: The number of this session. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and has no relation to any protocol value.
hwRsvpTeSessionNumber.name: hwRsvpTeSessionNumber

hwRsvpTeSessionReceivers.description: The number of reservations being requested of this system for this session.
hwRsvpTeSessionReceivers.name: hwRsvpTeSessionReceivers

hwRsvpTeSessionRequests.description: The number of reservation requests this system is sending upstream for this session.
hwRsvpTeSessionRequests.name: hwRsvpTeSessionRequests

hwRsvpTeSessionSenders.description: The number of distinct senders currently known to be part of this session.
hwRsvpTeSessionSenders.name: hwRsvpTeSessionSenders

hwRsvpTeSessionStyle.description: An enumerable value to identify the treatment of reservations for different senders within the same session: WF 10001b, FF01010b, SE 10010b.
hwRsvpTeSessionStyle.name: hwRsvpTeSessionStyle

hwRsvpTeSessionTable.description: A table of all sessions seen by a given sys- tem.
